President Trump delivered remarks at the White House Conference on Supporting Veterans and Military Families. He expressed his gratitude for the service of veterans and highlighted the actions his administration has taken to improve care and support for them. These actions include signing the VA Accountability Act to hold employees accountable, signing the Veterans Choice Act to provide veterans with access to private healthcare, and securing funding for mental health services and suicide prevention. President Trump also mentioned the record military funding his administration has secured and praised the strength and capabilities of the US military. He emphasized the importance of supporting service members and veterans and expressed his commitment to continuing to improve their care and support.